cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on the deployment of drone base stations in wireless networks and investigates the impact of different types of wireless backhaul on network performance. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with the placement of drone base stations, which involves robotics and control aspects. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of wireless backhaul on network performance, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The placement of drone base stations involves control and optimization aspects, which fall under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of drone base stations to enhance network coverage and area capacity, which can be related to multimedia applications.
